==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Carmelite
<hw>Car"mel*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A friar of a mendicant order (the Order of Our Lady of
Mount Carmel) established on Mount Carmel, in Syria, in the twelfth
century; a White Friar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A nun of the Order of Our lady of Mount
Carmel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Car mile</ent>⟦br⟧
